title: The MacPorts
layout: post
---
One of the best things I found is [MacPorts](http://www.macports.org/). As it says "The MacPorts Project is an open-source community initiative to design an easy-to-use system for compiling, installing, and upgrading either command-line, X11 or Aqua based open-source software on the Mac OS X operating system". 
<!-- more start -->
For apt-get lovers, like myself, this is awesome. You get your equivalente to apt-get or yum or pacman or what else you like. Download the .dmg and you're ready to go.


Here is a short list of apt-get commands in ports:

<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>$ sudo apt-get update</code></td>
<td><code>$ sudo port selfupdate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>$ sudo apt-get install cmus</code></td>
<td><code>$ sudo port install cmus</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>$ sudo apt-get remove cmus</code></td>
<td><code>$ sudo port uninstall cmus</code></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
[Link](http://www.macports.org/)
<!-- more end -->
